The skin is always the starting point with any makeup or the no make up look.  So making sure it’s prepped and primed to perfection is key.  I have such a busy schedule and oftentimes  it’s go go go.  Forma facial is the best choice for us busy ladies! 

No injecting. No cutting. No pain.  There is no downtime and is often referred to as a “lunch-time” facial treatment.  This non-invasive procedure uses heat and radio-frequency technology to stimulate deep beneath the skin.  It gently helps the body’s ability to produce collagen and elastin, as a result it will firm up and tighten skin, reduce fine lines and puffiness. 

Loved my visit at @doctorrahimd her clinic is conveniently located on Bedford in Beverly Hills.  Aesthetician: @angelenergy.aesthetics

Coucou (pronounced koo-koo) is a way of saying hello in French.  It is also the name of a brand-new concept in Venice Beach and last night was opening night!  Coucou celebrates aperitif culture and artisanal cocktails alongside dishes cooked over a wood-fire grill.  Inspired by the timeless bistros of France, the concept promises to honor the locale by embracing a coastal California vibes, showcasing the abundance of high-quality local farmers market offerings.
 
The menu was a playful balance of French-leaning favorites.  I love the Moules Mariniere & steak frites.  I highly recommend the ceviche(you are welcome!), the market crudités is a great way to get your kids to eat their veggies!  A plate full of colorful veggies and edible flowers 💗 

The perfect place to gather your girls for a night of get-together.  The cocktail menu is a must-see/must-try.  I love espresso martini so I had to try their spin to this iconic cocktail and wow, it was martini-riffic!  Don’t leave without capping your meal with the heavenly soft-serve(you are welcome!). Bonjour and welcome to the Coucou club 🍸🍹. Hayley Feldman(pictured) own and operate this new bistro alongside her husband Jesse.  She’s also a mom of 2! 

📍 @bar.coucou 

#coucouLA #LADining #dinela #aperitif #frenchbistro #artisanalcocktails #venicebeachrestaurant #veniceeats
#WhereToDineinLA

Today, I’m going to be sporting some Sonny Vaccaro energy 😎 

Last night’s special screening of AIR—What an impactful story-telling and beautifully made film.  The high caliber acting, I laugh, I cried and chair danced.  Set in 1984, with incredible 80’s music injected throughout the movie.  Matt Damon played Sonny Vaccaro, who is the persistent dreamer making a massive bet that should never work and basically succeeds due to his passion and drive.  Viola Davis…wow..impeccable acting. 

Synopsis:
From award-winning director Ben Affleck, AIR reveals the unbelievable game-changing partnership between a then-rookie Michael Jordan and Nike’s fledgling basketball division which revolutionized the world of sports and contemporary culture with the Air Jordan brand. This moving story follows the career-defining gamble of an unconventional team with everything on the line, the uncompromising vision of a mother who knows the worth of her son’s immense talent, and the basketball phenom who would become the greatest of all time. 🏀

AIR opens in theaters, April 5th

#airmovie @airmovie @amazonstudios @talentconnectgroup

To my precious children, on this Mother's Day and every day, I want to say thank you for making me a mom. Being your mom is the greatest gift I have ever received, and I am so grateful for the love, laughter, and joy you bring into my life. Watching you grow and flourish into the incredible individuals you are becoming is a privilege and an honor.

As a mother of two, my heart is filled with so much love and pride for the amazing human beings you are. You have taught me so much about patience, resilience, and unconditional love, and I am forever grateful for the lessons you continue to teach me every day.

On this special day, I also want to extend my gratitude to all the mothers out there who work tirelessly to raise their children with love, compassion, and grace. You are superheroes in our lives, and I am proud to stand alongside you in this amazing journey called motherhood.

Happy Mother's Day to all the incredible moms out there, and thank you to my children for making me the luckiest and happiest mom in the world! 

♥️

#mom #mama #mommy #mothersday

I had the EMS(electrical muscle stimulation) When using EMS, your body’s muscles will contract 20,000 times in one 30 minute session. That is the equivalent of doing 20,000 crunches or squats in a single session! 

Loved the infrared lymphatic drainage for my second treatment.  The far infrared treatment raises the body temperature, as the body warms, to cool itself down, it will sweat, increase blood circulation and the basic metabolic rate, it is a natural and fast way for weight loss.  Improves sleep, and is effective for relaxation, activates metabolism and clears the body of toxins and waste products.

Long days at the office doesn't mean you have to give up on your daily fitness goals! As shown by the lovely @classyverse 😍😍

The #eTrainingHopper can be moved wherever you need it!

The simple seated pedaling movement makes it extremely easy to multi-task, giving people the option to fit in a full lower body workout without sacrificing time away from their other endeavors.  The pedaling motion, coupled with #EMS technology, stimulates the muscles in your legs to contract and release several hundred times during the course of the workout.  This not only tones your legs but also improves blood and lymphatic circulation—perfect for those who have had to stand for long hours as well!

Unable to pedal while typing?  No problem!  Just rest your feet on the device with the EMS on, and that's more than enough to see some results. It doesn't get any easier than this.

Deep gratitude to Villagio Coldiretti, I Love Italian Food Organization, Italian Trade Agency, Filiera Italia, Campagna Amica, and TrenItalia for orchestrating such a phenomenal event.  A heartfelt thanks for having me; connecting with Italian product producers, manufacturers, family-owned farmers, and artisans has been an enlightening experience.  For many years, I’ve been fervently committed to championing authentic Italian products with DOP, DOC, DOCG, IDT, and IGP designations, emphasizing the need to combat those mimicking the true essence of “Italian made.” Let’s stand united in celebrating and preserving the authenticity of Italy’s rich culinary legacy. 🇮🇹
